ay be able to apply for a court order to restore a company if:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you did business with them </li>\n  <li>you worked for them</li>\n  <li>they owed you money when they were dissolved</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re responsible for their employee pension fund</li>\n  <li>you have a shared or competing interest in land</li>\n  <li>you were a shareholder or director when it was dissolved</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Except in cases of personal injury, you need to apply within 6 years of the company being dissolved.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can get <a href=\"/get-information-about-a-company\" title=\"Get information about a dissolved company\">information about a dissolved company</a> from Companies House.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>How to apply</h2>\n\n<p>Use form N208 to apply for court order restoration in England and Wales.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.bl.justice.gov.uk/courtfinder/forms/n208-eng.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form 208, claim to restore by court order'\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form 208, claim to restore by court order’ (PDF, 117KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/courtfinder/forms/n208a-eng.pdf\" title=\"How to complete the form to have a company restored\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form 208a, guidance notes’ (PDF, 437KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Send your completed form to the nearest county court to the company&rsquo;s registered office that deals with bankruptcy (select &lsquo;County Court&rsquo; under &lsquo;Search by court type&rsquo; in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/\" title=\"Her Majesty’s Courts &amp; Tribunal Service\">court finder</a>), or the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/Search.do?court_id=716\" title=\"Royal Courts of Justice\">Royal Courts of Justice.</a></p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also need to include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n