 England and Wales (but not Cornwall or Lancashire), the Treasury Solicitor looks after dissolved company assets. Use the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.bonavacantia.gov.uk/output/dissolved-company-notification-form.aspx\" title=\"dissolved company notification form\">dissolved company notification form</a> to refer an asset to the Treasury Solicitor.</p>\n\n<p>You can also write to:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nTreasury Solicitor's Office (BV)\n<br />1 Kemble Street\n<br />London \n<br />WC2B 4TS\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2>Other bodies that represent the Crown</h2>\n\n<p>Elsewhere, dissolved companies&rsquo; assets are dealt with by:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>in Cornwall and Lancashire - <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.farrer.co.uk/\" title=\"Farrer and Co\">Farrer and Co</a></li>\n  <li>in Scotland - <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://qltr.gov.uk/content/bona-vacantia\" title=\"The Queen's and Lord Treasurer's Remembrancer\">The Queen&rsquo;s and Lord Treasurer&rsquo;s Remembrancer</a></li>\n  <li>in Northern Ireland - phone or write to the Crown Solicitor&rsquo;s Office for Northern Ireland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Crown Solicitor’s Office for Northern Ireland</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><strong>Phone:</strong> 028 9054 6037</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nCrown Solicitor\n<br />Royal Courts of Justice\n<br />Chichester Street\n<br />Belfast \n<br />BT1 3JY\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/claiming-money-or-property-from-dissolved-company/discretionary-grants-for-shareholders","slug":"discretionary-grants-for-shareholders","order":4,"title":"Discretionary grants for shareholders","body":"<p>You may be able to get back a dissolved company&rsquo;s assets if you were one of its shareholders - apply for a discretionary grant.</p>\n\n<h2>How to apply</h2>\n\n<p>In England and Wales (but not Cornwall or Lancashire) you must apply to the Tr