d, go to court or make someone bankrupt if a person or business owes you money.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If someone owes you money and hasn’t arranged to pay it back after you’ve spoken or written to them, mediation is an option.</p>\n\n<h2>Mediation</h2>\n\n<p>Mediation is when an impartial person - trained in dealing with difficult discussions between 2 opposing sides - acts like a referee in a dispute.</p>\n\n<p>There can be a fee for mediation but it is cheaper than hiring a solicitor and taking court action. The fee is based on how much is owed.</p>\n\n<p>You can <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.civilmediation.justice.gov.uk/\" title=\"Find a mediation service\">find a mediation process online</a> to start the process. Use the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.scottishmediation.org.uk/find-a-mediator\" title=\"Scottish Mediation Network - find a mediator\">Scottish Mediation Network</a> if you&rsquo;re in Scotland.</p>\n\n<h2>Court action</h2>\n\n<p>If mediation doesn&rsquo;t work, you can make a <a href=\"make-court-claim-for-money/overview\" title=\"Take your claim to court\">court claim for your money</a>.</p>\n\n<p>If the money owed is less than £100,000 and owed by no more than 2 people or 2 organisations, you can make a <a href=\"/make-money-claim-online\" title=\"Make a money claim online\">claim online</a>. </p>\n\n<p>The court can order the money to be paid. </p>\n\n<h2>Making someone bankrupt if they can&rsquo;t pay</h2>\n\n<p>You can use a <a href=\"/statutory-demands\" title=\"Find out more about statutory demands\">statutory demand</a> to ask for money you&rsquo;re owed. </p>\n\n<p>If the person who owes you money ignores the statutory demand or can&rsquo;t repay the money, you can ask a court to <a href=\"/creditor-bankruptcy-petitions\" title=\"Making someone bankrupt\">make them bankrupt</a> (but only if your owed more than £750). </p>\n\n<p>However, the costs are high and you may not get any of your money back.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application