ve written in the petition is true. You can buy one from a legal stationers.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.insolvencydirect.bis.gov.uk/forms/ew/Form4-02.doc\" title=\"Download a winding up petition form\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form 4.2, winding up petition’ (DOC, 40KB).</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You need certain details about the company (eg the registered office address), you can get these from <a href=\"/get-information-about-a-company\" title=\"Get information about a company\">Companies House</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Fees</h2>\n\n<p>The fees are:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>£220 - court fees</li>\n  <li>£1,165 - petition deposit (for managing the &lsquo;winding up&rsquo;)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You might be able get the fees back if the company can afford to repay them. </p>\n\n<p>You can pay using cash, postal orders or a building society, bank or solicitor’s cheque made payable to Her Majesty’s Courts &amp; Tribunal Service.</p>\n\n<h3>Where to send the petition</h3>\n\n<p>If the company has a &lsquo;paid up share capital&rsquo; of more than £120,000 (this will be shown in the company information) send the petition to the High Court. </p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nThe High Court\n<br />Royal Courts of Justice\n<br />Companies Court\n<br />TM 2.09\n<br />Strand\n<br />London\n<br />WC2A 2LL\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<p>For other companies, use the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.bl.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/\" title=\"Find your local court\">court finder</a> to find a court dealing with insolvency. You must use a court nearest to the company&rsquo;s registered office.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/wind-up-a-company-that-owes-you-money/the-court-hearing","slug":"the-court-hearing","order":3,"title":"The court hearing","body":"<p>If the court accepts your petition, they’ll arrange a date for a hearing.</p>\n\n<p>You need to serve the winding up petition by:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>delivering it to the company’s registered office</li>\n  <li>sending it by registered post</li>\n  <li>paying a process serving company to do it</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>To prove that the petition was served, send a &lsquo;certificate of personal service&rsquo; to the court where you submitted the petition.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bis.gov.uk/assets/insolvency/docs/forms/ew/form6-11.doc\" title=\"Download 'Form 6.11, certificate of personal service of statutory demand' (DOC, 40KB)\">Download ‘Form 6.11, certificate of personal service of statutory demand’ (DOC, 40KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>What happens next</h3>\n\n<p>At least 7 working days before the hearing, place an advert <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/place-notice\" title=\"How to place an advert in the London Gazette\">in the London Gazette</a> saying the petition has been served.</p>\n\n<p>At least 5 working days before the hearing, send a copy of the advertisement and a certificate of compliance to the court.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bis.gov.uk/assets/insolvency/docs/forms/ew/form4-07.doc\" title=\"Download 'Form 4.7, certificate of compliance' (DOC, 50KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form 4.7, certificate of compliance’ (DOC, 50KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>At the hearing</h2>\n\n<p>You must bring a list of everyone who will be attending the hearing. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bis.gov.uk/assets/insolvency/docs/forms/ew/form4-10.doc\" title=\"Download 'Form 4.10, list of people attending a hearing' (DOC, 47KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form 4.10, list of people attending a hearing’ (DOC, 47KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If the petition is successful, the company will be wound up and put into liquidation. </p>\n\n<p>The liquidator will decide if and how any available funds are distributed to creditors.</p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Funding and debt","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business%2Ffunding